-- Global Funds Sell Net 4.99 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2011-02-09T03:53:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/global-funds-sell-net-4-99-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global funds sold a net 4.99 billion
rupees ($110 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  yesterday,
according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.9 percent to 936.1 billion rupees, or 34.3
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 7.27 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
